The paper deals with clustering image-caption pairs, which involves both computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a method for learning image and text representations, which involves machine learning (ML) techniques such as stacked autoencoders and Kullback-Leibler divergence minimization. Therefore, cs.LG and cs.IR are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with multi-modal data, which involves multimedia (MM) techniques. Therefore, cs.MM is also a likely sub-category.
